NTUTHUKO Shoba took the witness stand on Monday, 14 February after his discharge application to the High Court in Joburg was refused. Shoba is accused of ordering his pregnant girlfriend Tshegofatso Pule’s murder in June 2020. He said it was not Pule’s first pregnancy. “She first got pregnant in 2019. We were both shocked and we agreed we would terminate,” he said When asked about Malephane, Shoba told the court they didn’t have a close relationship. He said he got Malephane’s number during the first lockdown. “He told me he sold liquor and cigarettes. I told him I’d get his number so that I could buy cigarettes from him,” he said. The matter will continue on Tuesday, 15 February.